# Dataset Information for ESL Sentiment Analysis

1. TOEFL11 Corpus
   - Description: Essays written by non-native English speakers taking the TOEFL exam.
   - Source: https://www.cambridge.org/engage/api-gateway/toefl/assets/orp/resource/item/64003c4c1a682dceaeaa5f8f/original/toefl11.pdf
   - Usage: Used to analyze sentiment and formal/informal writing tone.

2. ICNALE (International Corpus Network of Asian Learners of English)
   - Description: Essays from Asian English learners with proficiency levels.
   - Source: http://language.sakura.ne.jp/icnale/
   - Usage: Helps classify sentiment patterns in Asian ESL writing.

3. Lang-8 Learner Corpus
   - Description: Texts written by ESL learners, corrected by native speakers.
   - Source: http://www.phontron.com/lang8/
   - Usage: Used to compare raw vs. corrected sentiment differences.

4. ICLE (International Corpus of Learner English)
   - Description: Academic essays from ESL students of various backgrounds.
   - Source: https://www.uclouvain.be/en/research-institutes/ilc/icle.html
   - Usage: Formal vs. informal sentiment detection.

5. ESL-4 Dataset
   - Description: Four English proficiency tasks for reading, writing, listening.
   - Source: https://www.nist.gov/itl/iad/mig/esl-4-corpus
   - Usage: Sentiment analysis on ESL responses.

6. Quora Question Pairs Dataset
   - Description: A dataset of similar questions for text similarity.
   - Source: https://www.kaggle.com/qcri/corpus
   - Usage: Analyzing sentiment shifts in question rewording.

